What a rip-off. None of their pre-made salads sounded appealing, but I saw a make you option that was under $7. Perfect, or so I thought. You get to choose your base and up to four toppings. Got my base and started with some cucumber and carrots. I asked for egg, but it was extra. I asked for cheese, but it was extra. I asked for roasted vegetables, but they were extra, as was the the avocado and anything that could be considered a protein. It was ridiculous. It became a joke as I could not even get my four included toppings because everything cost extra.  I would have given 1 star, but the service was decent and at least he told me everything was extra before he added it to my salad. One to the most expensive salads with practically nothing on it. There are much better and less expensive options. I won't be going back.

I’ll be honest, sweetgreen doesn’t feel like a great value.  After all, you theoretically *could* make a salad for way cheaper. Right? Let’s be realistic. Could you?  Let’s say you want to make a grade-A salad. You need to get a pound of kale, some seeds, a nice dressing, a bunch of different veggies, make some grains, beans, a couple avocados, and some purple cabbage to give it some jazz.  That’s going to cost you $40+ and half will realistically go bad. You’re not actually going to eat all of that salad. Plus, you have to actually make it.  It’s much more cost-efficient to just go out and get that awesome salad 2-3 times a week when you actually want it and pay $10. This is exactly where sweetgreen comes in.

But the best part is how genuinely friendly the staff is. Whenever I have the choice, I always choose Sweetgreen because I know I can rely on their exemplary customer service.

SweetGreen's salads were alright. I still feel ridiculous paying 10 bucks for a bunch of leaves, a small amount of other various vegetables, and a bit of sauce but college students always have to say they tried trendy places right?  Their salad is a lot smaller than Chop't, but the interior of this place is really cool. The seats are nice, the coat hangers are from real trees and everything is environmentally friendly, making you feel less guilty about leaving a carbon footprint when you eat out.  If you want to dine in at a salad place, this is the place to go. If you want to take it out, go to Chop't.  Side note: this place plays really good music. yet another reason to dine in.

Worst way to 'lose' $8.36. I could have gone to the grocery store and gotten more for under $3. I am an avid veggie eater and have at least 6 salads a week and this is the first time I wanted to throw one away. This was the first time I'd ever been to a Sweetgreen and I can say without a shadow of a doubt that I WILL NOT BE GOING BACK!!!  Its over priced lettuce. Heck I would have been better off going to Whole Foods at least there you can mix in whatever you want and decide how much lettuce you're actually gonna have.  Although the bowls they use are pretty large, they fill it to the top with 'greens' then push it down to add the 4 ingredients that you get for free, which of course is barely anything at all anyway. Then any extra add-ins that you want will cost you $0.50. The cheese is all over $1 for a minuscule amount. And the dressings are way to tangy and oily.  Also, the staff were all a little to uppity. Acting like they were better than me cause they eat healthier all the time since I had never been there before. Then acting extremely annoyed when I show absolute shock after they tell me that my small salad is $8.36.  If I could rate this with zero stars I would most definitely do it. I would never recommend this place anyone!!

The atmosphere is the weak spot, but that's unavoidable due to the location.
